Explanation: According to all the documents, the subject of the film "The Right Stuff" is indeed related to Project Mercury. While the documents mention different aspects of Project Mercury and the film (e.g., its protagonists, the first American astronauts; the test pilot Chuck Yeager; Tom Wolfe's book about it), they consistently confirm that Project Mercury is a central theme in the film.

In particular, document 50.txt mentions: "The Right Stuff follows test pilots who were selected to be astronauts for NASA’s Project Mercury..."

Document 59.txt discusses how the cowboy qualities of fighter pilot Chuck Yeager were used in the film to counter the American back log after the Soviet Sputnik satellite and to adapt them to the more turbulent world of the 1980s, but still clearly connects it to Project Mercury.

Document 66.txt mentions that the new National Geographic miniseries about Project Mercury is based on Tom Wolfe’s 1979 book and the 1983 film "The Right Stuff".

Therefore, all documents support the triple that the subject of the film 'The Right Stuff' is indeed related to Project Mercury.
